{{Refimprove|date=December 2009}}
The '''Vasyugan Swamp''' ({{Lang-ru|Васюганские болота}}) is the largest [[swamps|swamp]] in the northern hemisphere. It is located in Russia, in [[West Siberian Plain|southwestern Siberia]].

The swamp is a major reservoir of [[fresh water]] for the region, and the [[Vasyugan River|Vasyugan river]] has its source there. It is home to a number of [[endangered species]] which is a concern among local [[environmentalist]]s as the production of [[Petroleum|oil]] and [[gas]] has become a major industry in the region.

==Location==
{{coord|57|34|N|75|39|E|source:kolossus-ruwiki|display=title}}
{{Location map | Russia 
| width    = 250
| float    = right
| caption  = Vasyugan swamp (Russia)
| alt      = Vasyugan swamp
| lat_deg  = 57.34
| lon_deg  = 75.39
}}

It occupies 53,000&nbsp;km²,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.poormojo.org/pmjadaily/archives/031554.php |title=Poor Mojo's Newswire: The Vasyugan swamp, the biggest swamp in the world |website=Poormojo.org |date=2010-05-12 |accessdate=2016-03-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120321214659/http://www.poormojo.org/pmjadaily/archives/031554.php |archivedate=2012-03-21 |df= }}</ref> which is about 2% of the whole area of [[peat bog]]s of the world. The swamp is located in the [[Novosibirsk Oblast|Novosibirsk]], [[Omsk Oblast|Omsk]], and [[Tomsk Oblast|Tomsk]] regions of [[Russia]] along the west bank of the [[Ob River]], and stretches between latitudes 55°35' and 58°40' North, and longitudes 74°30' and 83°30' East. It has about 800,000 small lakes in it. <ref>{{cite web |url=https://hague6185.wordpress.com/2013/10/14/vasyugan-swamp-western-siberia-russia/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2016-12-24 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161224170557/https://hague6185.wordpress.com/2013/10/14/vasyugan-swamp-western-siberia-russia/ |archivedate=2016-12-24 |df= }}</ref>

==History==
It appeared nearly 10,000 years ago and from that time has constantly increased in size. 75% of the contemporary area became waterlogged less than 500 years ago.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.greenpeace.org/russia/en/campaigns/world-natural-heritage/great-vasyugan-mire/ |title=Great Vasyugan Mire &#124; Greenpeace Russia |website=Greenpeace.org |date= |accessdate=2016-03-01 |deadurl=no |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160305022156/http://www.greenpeace.org/russia/en/campaigns/world-natural-heritage/great-vasyugan-mire/ |archivedate=2016-03-05 |df= }}</ref>

==Climate==
The swamp has a [[continental climate]] ([[Biome#Walter system|Walter system]]) or [[taiga]] ([[World Wide Fund for Nature|WWF system]]),<ref>{{cite web|title=Taiga or Boreal Forest|url=http://www.radford.edu/~swoodwar/CLASSES/GEOG235/biomes/taiga/taiga.html |accessdate=February 21, 2011|deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110609021800/http://www.radford.edu/~swoodwar/CLASSES/GEOG235/biomes/taiga/taiga.html |archivedate=June 9, 2011 }}</ref> with long cold winters and short hot summers.

